.TH GAT-DX 1 "2026-06-04" "gat 0.3.0" "gat Manual"
.SH NAME
gat-dx \- enter or run a worktree-scoped Docker container
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B gat dx
.RB [ \-\-service
.IR name ]
.RB [ \-\-doctor ]
.RB [ \-\- ]
.RI [ command ...]
.br
.B gat docker
.RI [ ... ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Finds a running container whose bind mount source matches the current worktree
root and
.B exec
s into it; if none is running, falls back to
.B docker compose run \-\-rm <service>
from the worktree's compose directory. With no command, runs
.BR bash .
Service selection uses
.BR \-\-service ,
then
.IR GAT_DOCKER_SERVICE ,
then
.IR gat.dockerService ,
then the
.I dp1
default, then the only runnable declared service.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-\-service " name"
Compose service to exec into or run.
.TP
.B \-\-doctor
Print Docker/worktree diagnostics instead of running a command.
.TP
.B \-\-
Treat everything after as the command to run.
.SH EXAMPLES
.RS
.EX
gat dx
gat dx \-\- npm test
gat dx \-\-service web \-\- bash
gat dx \-\-doctor
.EE
.RE
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR gat (1),
.BR gat\-config (1)
